# DevX 2.0 - Development Guide

## UI Conventions

When creating or modifying pages, follow these patterns:

### Page Layout
- All pages use `<div className="flex-1 space-y-6 p-6">` as the main container
- Always use the `<PageHeader>` component from `@/components/ui/page-header` for page titles
- Use `p-6` padding (24px) everywhere — never `px-6 py-4`
- No `container`, `max-w-*`, or `mx-auto` on page wrappers

### PageHeader Usage
```tsx
import { PageHeader } from "@/components/ui/page-header";
import { IconName } from "lucide-react";

<PageHeader icon={IconName} title="Title" subtitle="Description" color="violet">
  <Button>Action</Button>  {/* optional right-side children */}
</PageHeader>
```
Colors: blue, violet, emerald, amber, rose, slate, orange, cyan

### Color Tokens (Dark Mode)
Never use hardcoded colors like `bg-white`, `text-gray-900`, `border-gray-200`.
Use: `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-muted`

### Card Style
Cards use `rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-border/40 border-l-[3px] border-l-{color}-500`

### Skeleton Loaders
Must match the actual content layout — same container, grid, card shapes.

## Project Structure
- Client pages: `client/src/pages/`
- UI components: `client/src/components/ui/`
- Feature modules: `client/src/components/{feature-name}/` (see Module Structure below)
- API calls: `apiRequest()` from `client/src/lib/queryClient.ts`
- Server routes: `server/routes.ts`
- Dev server: `npm run dev` (port 4000)

## Module Structure (Mandatory for complex features)

Any feature with more than ~400 lines **must** be a standalone module, not a single file. Follow the pattern established in `client/src/components/specs/`:

```
client/src/components/{feature}/
├── types.ts              # All TypeScript interfaces and type aliases
├── utils.ts              # Pure functions, constants, helpers (no React)
├── use-{concern}.ts      # Custom hooks — one per logical concern (queries, sync, generation, etc.)
├── {panel-name}.tsx      # Sub-components extracted from render functions
├── {dialog-name}.tsx     # Dialogs as standalone components
└── index.tsx             # Slim orchestrator: state + layout only (~300–500 lines)
```

### Rules
- **File size cap**: No single `.tsx` or `.ts` file over ~600 lines. Split at that point.
- **types.ts first**: Before writing any component, define all interfaces in `types.ts`.
- **utils.ts for pure logic**: Markdown generators, slug helpers, localStorage wrappers, config maps — never inline these in components.
- **Custom hooks for side effects**: Each `useQuery`/`useEffect` cluster with a clear concern goes into its own `use-*.ts` hook. E.g. `use-specs-generation.ts`, `use-repo-sync.ts`.
- **Sub-components for render functions**: Any `renderXxx()` function over ~50 lines becomes a named component in its own file with an explicit Props interface.
- **Dialogs are components**: Never inline dialog JSX in the parent; extract to `{name}-dialog.tsx`.
- **index.tsx is the orchestrator only**: It imports everything, manages shared state, and composes the layout. No inline render helpers, no large blocks of JSX.
- **Re-export from original path**: When moving a component to a new module, the original file becomes a single `export { X } from "@/components/{feature}";` so existing imports don't break.
- **Relative imports within a module**: Files inside the same module folder import each other with `./`, never with `@/components/{feature}/`.
